{"tid":1251030,"cid":33,"subCid":0,"title":"[ 文宣組準備? ] 大家覺得應唔應該廣傳 陳太 \"特赦哂義士+克警\" 既方案?","createTime":"2019-06-22T10:36:39.000Z","updateTime":"2019-06-25T13:23:22.000Z","uid":257422,"like":100,"dislike":5,"uniUserReply":29,"replies":[{"pid":"5f520d6f3411379cc70090d5620b606861a6d0fc","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:36:39.000Z","msg":"正評<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/bouncy.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 認同, 文宣組做野<br />\n負評<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/fire.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  唔認同<br />\n<br />\n陳方安生致林鄭月娥公開信<br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/1250929\" target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/1250929</a><br />\n<span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">1. 撤回法案<br />\n2. 成立獨立調查克警委員會 <br />\n3. 一次過特赦義士*以及濫權濫暴克警</span><br />\n*(陳太建議入面只係提到612, 咁我就當然覺得應該係69, 612 既所有義士啦)</span><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: x-large;\">大家認唔認同陳太既政治智慧?</span><br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c284384e698992f9488e7e5674757f9714786840","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:37:02.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9476103c81859871c1201ceb166425e29a9025cd","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:37:14.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"baed50946dead1ee0664ed8fb0e8324d01d4b362","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:37:34.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"dfbd37d3e5b9cc12a0239d62380683475bcb7d06","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:37:46.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9606a3b7e6e777e3301c7175b12396b23051170e","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:38:04.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"85a2f1e04c1520c6436f5a8b29baf4df88af6f97","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:38:14.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b66183d350a4ed7c5f403241ebe87b89d27729fa","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:38:24.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"303b48afa0b2a8e6feba6f7e366acc0608f6b67d","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:39:02.000Z","msg":"針對《逃犯條例》修訂引爆的危機及 6 月 12 日的警民衝突， 前政務司司長陳方安生今早發公開信給林鄭月娥，提出三點要求：<br />\n1. 撤回法案<br />\n2. 獨立調查委員會<br />\n3. 一次過特赦<br />\n<br />\nOpen Letter to the Chief Executive, Mrs. Carrie Lam<br />\n<br />\n22 June 2019<br />\n<br />\nThe Honourable Carrie Lam Cheng Yuet-ngor, GBM, CBS <br />\nChief Executive<br />\nOffice of the Chief Executive<br />\nHong Kong Special Administrative Region<br />\nPeople&rsquo;s Republic of China<br />\nTamar <br />\nHong Kong<br />\n<br />\nI am writing to you as a friend and former colleague who, like you, has devoted my whole career to the civil service and the welfare of Hong Kong people.<br />\n<br />\nI am not going to take time rehearsing, let alone allocating blame as to why Hong Kong finds itself in this crisis. As public servants, we all do our best for the people of Hong Kong, that is a given.<br />\n<br />\nHowever, I now urge you and your advisors to fully acknowledge the gravity of the current situation and show yourselves worthy of the trust that has been placed in you.<br />\n<br />\nI believe the following decisive steps are essential to defuse tension and restore lasting calm to our streets:<br />\n<br />\nTo stop juggling with semantics and state, categorically, that you are withdrawing the Fugitive Offenders and Mutual Legal Assistance in Criminal Matters Legislation (Amendment) Bill 2019; your refusal to do so only invites suspicion and fuels anger;<br />\n<br />\nTo establish a completely impartial Commission of Inquiry, chaired by a senior member of the Judiciary, into the circumstances of the disturbances on 12 June and the response of our police force. I believe this is vital, not just to acknowledge the deep concerns of the protesters and their families, but to restore the trust and respect of our community for a force that has maintained our safety and served us with courage and integrity for so many years. The officers in the front line should not be pilloried simply for following orders and doing what they believed was their duty to maintain law and order;<br />\n<br />\nTo consider offering a one-off amnesty to all involved in potentially criminal acts on 12 June: namely those who have been arrested and may be charged with riotous behaviour, those who may be charged at a later date and members of the police force who, while acting under orders, may be found to have used excessive force.<br />\n<br />\nOn the basis of these concessions, I believe you would be fully justified in expecting the community to refrain from further action that may lead to public disorder and disrupt the normal life of the city.<br />\n<br />\nAnson Chan, GBM, GCMG, CBE, JP<br />\nFormer Chief Secretary for Administration"},{"pid":"b42f8c53890620c69c02289655c5750c7615f667","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:39:14.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"ff6ffcfe780909ad9dcefbd085c08242d59acd1b","tid":1251030,"uid":257422,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-22T10:40:42.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"82